<item>
            <title>[JDK-8282319] java.util.Locale method to stream available Locales</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8282319</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>java.util.Local.getAvailableLocales returns an array of Locales.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
A method that returns java.util.stream.Stream&amp;lt;Locale&amp;gt; would be very useful to be able to filter and select Locales.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It could retain the Locales avoiding the necessity of a defensive copy of the Locale[].&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Or alternatively, return an un-modifiable Set and allow the caller to stream() it.</description>
